The paper deals with the problem of synthesizing soundtracks for silent videos using deep learning techniques. The paper involves the use of deep learning models such as RNNs and CNNs for sound prediction and generation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the use of computer vision techniques such as Temporal Relationship Networks (TRN) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for better understanding of the input-to-output associations over time. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques for sound prediction and generation, which falls under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
